description: TMC chief and West Bengal Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee showed black flags while going to take part in the Ganga Aarti at Dashashwamedh Ghat in Varanasi. The activists of Hindu Yuva Vahini chanted 'Jai Shri Ram' and 'Modi-Modi' and waved black flags to her. After landing at the Lal Bahadur Shastri International airport, she went straight to the ghat to see Ganga Aarti. When her vehicle was crossing through the Chetganj area, a group of Hindu Yuva Vahini workers started raising slogans like "wapas jao" (go back) and showing black flags. They were restrained by the police on the spot. To express her annoyance over the incident, she sat on the ghat steps instead of a chair and watched the Ganga Aarti.
